25/01/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A two-day meeting of defence ministers of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- wraps up Tuesday (25 January) behind closed doors. The local press reported that representatives of the United States, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Greece, Italy, Hungary, Romania, Slovenia, Serbia-Montenegro and Turkey are also attending. The focus of talks is reportedly on progress achieved by the Western Balkan countries in the process of NATO integration. 
In other news, Croatia and Norway signed a bilateral agreement on re-admission and co-operation against illegal migration. The agreement also provides for mutual protection of exchanged information between the respective interior ministries. (HRT, Fena - 24/01/05) 
